Countries need to develop a level of "risk tolerance" in dealing with each other, says Prof Jia Qingguo, Professor, School of International Studies, Peking University, at the #SingaporeSummit.

He also rejected the notion that the world is becoming bifurcated and hoped that the U.S. will be more pragmatic in policymaking. 

